[21:33] <AlexDaniel> bazzaar: yes

[21:34] <AlexDaniel> bazzaar: there is a list of different ways to write pairs here: https://docs.perl6.org/type/Pair

[21:34] <AlexDaniel> bazzaar: in theory, .perl can use any of them, as long as it is valid code :)

[21:34] <bazzaar> AlexDaniel: thanks for clearing that up, I'd have been staring at that for the next month of Sundays :)

[21:35] <AlexDaniel> bazzaar: if want to output this for users, it is probably better to stringify it yourself the way you want

[21:35] <AlexDaniel> bazzaar: I don't think we even have any guarantees as to what .perl will give exactly, so it may change

